# Queues and cron

## Queues (BullMQ)

Location: app/server/queues/* and app/server/clients/queuesClient.ts

- backupQueue.ts — database or file backup orchestration (paired with /api/tasks/backup)
- plaidSyncQueue.ts — primary Plaid transaction syncing
- plaidSyncBalanceQueue.ts — Plaid balance refreshes
- recalculateQueue.ts — forecast and derived-data recalculation

Guidelines:
- Enqueue from API or cron when work is non-trivial or external
- Log integration operations with IntegrationJobLog (recordIntegrationJobLog.ts)
- Keep job names stable; include dedupe keys where appropriate

## Cron (nuxt-cron)

Location: app/server/cron/*

- backup.daily.ts
- plaid.daily.ts
- plaid-balance.hourly.ts
- recalculate.hourly.ts
- bill-reminders.hourly.ts
- crypto-balance.hourly.ts

Notes:
- Cron tasks should be idempotent and quick to schedule; offload heavy work to queues
- Use server/env.ts flags to disable certain crons in CI as needed (see tests covering cronDisabled)

## Microservice background

- microservice/lib/bull.ts present for job infra; the microservice focuses on migration/rotation routes
- Key-rotation CronJob image (runner-keyrotate) bundles kubectl + script to patch secrets and call /migrate
